rivatised plants in the Romanian steel industry and Ukraine's civil machine-building sector in the 2000s.This book should be relevant for anyone taking interest in how and to what extent workers can reassert their influence over the conditions of production in regions and economic sectors characterised by disinvestment (of which outsourcing and ‘lean’ methods of production are instances).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLabor movementzRomania. 0aLabor movementzUkraine. 0aPost-communismzRomania. 0aPost-communismzUkraine. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aFactory.  aInterest representation.  aPost-communist Europe.  aRomania.  aStrategy.  aStrike.  aTrade unions.  aUkraine.1 aVarga, Mihai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packagez978311128357940uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611249140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526112491423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526112491/original  a978-3-11-128357-9  Manchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packageb2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles